replies.body:
:P marksmen buy assassin items because assassin items give them more attack damage, but they cant buy 6 assassin items without sacrificing their role so really if you take all of the assassin items and remove penetration and attack damage and movement speed  and start over new there'd still be players who value assassin items over marksman items on a ranged champion. league is set up to where anyone can buy anything in the game and i like that about it

smite for example is so nit-picky about what a player can and cannot buy that it could be played by lee sin in the dark without turtle beaches. that game separates every character into magic or physical and ranged or melee. then from there you can buy only items of your 2 classes.

league on the other hand doesnt do that and im glad it doesnt because that stifles creativity and makes every game feel the same.

champions are created in league so far with just ranged vs melee to determine their items. with hydra and runaans being the only locked item besides smite sticks that build from machete.

i think the real problem is that while this one item is made specifically for assassin's the fact is that this game promotes free will and as long as an item has more damage than another item with 6 item slots to fill it's going to show up on players builds. a really good way to fix this issue would be to offer items that marksmen would rather buy over this item. currently many of the stats in game dont feel as powerful as "deleting" an enemy with a single basic attack or Q. if the stats on our masteries could somehow end up on items like putting fervor on a new item that grants 20% attack speed or something and we lowered base attack speed on all items overall so that 2.5 was harder to hit for marksmen we could start dropping base numbers on a lot of items and marksmen physical damage scalings to make attack speed and critical be more important on their builds. then assassin's could buy their high damage items and marksmen could buy their high attack speed items and some of the players who like hybrid assassin marksmen would pick from both trees.

i'll give you a chart of items and stats and show you what i mean. this is going to seem like a wall of text but i hope it helps me express my views.


what marksmen are expected to want - attack speed, critical, attack damage, movement speed.
what assassins are expected to want - damage, penetration, cooldown reduction, movement speed.

