now if the same thing applies here as does with marksmen having an item in more than one place would seem appealing to an assassin. however because the assassin needs such basic stats (everyone wants cooldown and everyone wants damage and everyone wants movement speed and everyone wants penetration) almost all of the items in the game would give something to an assassin so the choices are a bit more convoluted - for example what assassin buys ardent censor? nidalee maybe? idk.

my point is that there arent enough items to keep the marksmen from wanting damage. basic stats are too commonly distributed in items. in theory if you have 2.5 attack speed at 100 damage you're doing the same amount of damage as someone who has 250 damage at 1.0 attack speed (i think unless there's a hidden variable in the math formula like there is with resistances). critical strikes are convoluted in their efficiency so many players wont even use them since armor penetration and damage are on the same items usually and it guarantees more damage per shot. i recommend changing all marksmen from physical damage scaling to critical and attack speed scaling for their abilities or substantially dropping their power on their abilities to compensate for the spike of basic attack damage they get. now of course this is all depending upon how each individual champion plays, but for the most part i think this is a good explanation of player item choice. if you take a look at the items you'll see that duskblade has the highest physical damage available because of the physical damage at 75 damage and 10 penetration the next runner ups would be {{item:3072}} {{item:3508}} {{item:3031}} {{item:3142}}

until critical/attack speed is changed or duskblade is changed to be less of an offensive item and more of a passive item i dont think it's going to change who buys if riot wants it to be bought at all.

there are ranged assassin's who'd be missing out if it were to be made into a melee only weapon. that would then cause problems with those specific champs and their roles in the game.
